-- El Salvador to Get $200 Million IDB Loan for Climate Change
-- B y   B i l l   F a r i e s
-- 2012-03-13T19:16:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/el-salvador-to-get-200-million-idb-loan-for-climate-change.html
El Salvador  will receive a $200
million loan from the  Inter-American Development Bank  to improve
tax collection and address the impact of  climate change .  The 20-year loan from the Washington-based lender carries a
variable interest rate based on the London interbank offered
rate and comes with a five-year grace period, the IDB said in a
statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bill Faries in Buenos Aires at 
 wfaries@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Richard Jarvie at 
 rjarvie@bloomberg.net  